CollectiveAccess Openshift 1.1
==============================

Create a free Red Hat Openshift account: https://openshift.redhat.com    

Getting started: https://openshift.redhat.com/app/getting_started

CollectiveAccess installation: http://wiki.collectiveaccess.org/index.php?title=Installation_%28Providence%29

INSTALLATION
============

1) rhc-create-domain -n domain -l email
2) rhc-create-app -a collectiveaccess -t php-5.3 -l email 
3) cd collectiveaccess
4) git pull git@github.com:bramw/openshiftcollectiveaccess.git 
5) rhc-ctl-app -a collect2 -e add-cron-1.4 -l email 
6) Rhc-ctl-app -a collectiveaccess -e add-mysql-5.1 -l email  
7) cd php and edit setup.php with database configuration from step 6 and change timezone and admin e-mail
	define("__CA_DB_HOST__", "DB host");
	define("__CA_DB_USER__", "admin");
	define("__CA_DB_PASSWORD__", "DB Password");
	define("__CA_DB_DATABASE__", "collectiveaccess");
	date_default_timezone_set("Europe/Brussels");
	define("__CA_ADMIN_EMAIL__", "email"); 
8) git add setup.php
9) git commit -m "setup.php"
10) git push
11) Finish CollectiveAccess installation on http://collectiveaccess-domain.rhcloud.com/install (change domain in domain from step 1)
